# Wiki Identity Parsing Rule

## Scope

Transforms a Limbus Company wiki.gg identity page into structured markdown.
Input: URL or fetched content from `https://limbuscompany.wiki.gg/wiki/<Identity_Page>`.
Output: `docs/parsed-ids/<Identity_Name>.md` (underscores, no sinner name prefix from the association — use the identity's distinguishing name).

Reference file: `docs/parsed-ids/Ring_Apprentice_Faust.md`.

## Content Extraction (MUST)

### Strip (DO NOT include)

- Navigation menus, sidebars, search bars
- Gallery / sprite / animation sections
- Trivia section
- Uptie details section
- "Retrieved from" footer
- Cookie notices
- Repeated tooltip definition blocks (wiki duplicates tooltip text dozens of times at page bottom)
- Resistance table (icon-only data, not available in text)
- Damage type per skill — Slash/Pierce/Blunt (icon-only data, not available in text)
- Sanity factors and Panic type tables (boilerplate shared across all identities)

### Keep

- Identity name, flavor quote, rarity, season, release date, traits
- Base stats: HP, Speed range, Defense Level
- Stagger Thresholds
- All unique / identity-specific status effects and mechanics
- All attack skills (both states if multi-state identity)
- All defense skills (Guard, Evade, Counter)
- All combat passives
- Support passive
- Referenced external mechanics not described elsewhere in the document

## Output Format (MUST)

Sections MUST appear in the following order. Omit conditional sections when criteria are not met.

### 1. Header Block

```markdown
# <Full Identity Name>

> *"<Flavor quote from the identity page>"*

**Rarity:** <Rarity>  
**Season:** <Season name>  
**Release:** <YYYY.MM.DD>  
**Traits:** <Comma-separated trait list>

---
```

### 2. Base Stats

```markdown
## Base Stats

| HP | Speed | Defense Level |
|----|-------|---------------|
| <HP> | <Min>–<Max> | <DefLvl> |

**Stagger Thresholds:** <Pct1>% (<Abs1>) — <Pct2>% (<Abs2>) [— <Pct3>% (<Abs3>)]

---
```

- Speed: use en-dash `–` between min and max (DO NOT use tilde `~`).
- Stagger Thresholds: use em-dash `—` between entries. Include all thresholds present on the wiki page.

### 3. Key Status Effects (CONDITIONAL)

Include ONLY when the identity has **unique, identity-specific mechanics** (e.g., Iron Maiden, Flow State, Corpus Ingredient, Artwork: Fascia).

DO NOT include standard game-wide mechanics listed in `docs/status-effects.md` (e.g., Poise, Bleed, Burn, Tremor, Rupture, Sinking, Charge, Haste, Bind, Defense Level Up/Down, Offense Level Up/Down, Damage Up/Down).

```markdown
## Key Status Effects

### <Effect Name>
- <Bullet-point description>
- **<Trigger>:** <Effect>

---
```

Source: tooltip blocks at the bottom of the wiki page. Deduplicate — each unique effect appears once.

OMIT this entire section for identities with no unique mechanics.

### 4. Attack Skills

**Single-state identity:**

```markdown
## Skills
```

**Multi-state identity** (identity has distinct skill sets per state):

```markdown
## Skills — <State Name>
```

One section per state. Each skill within:

```markdown
### Skill <N>: <Skill Name>

| Offense Level | Base Power | Coin Power | Atk Weight |
|---------------|------------|------------|------------|
| <OL> (<Base>+<Bonus>) | <BP> | +<CP> | x<W> |

**[On Use]** <Effect description>

| Coin | Effects |
|------|---------|
| 1 | <Coin 1 effects, semicolon-separated if multiple> |
| 2 | <Coin 2 effects> |

---
```

- Offense Level: raw value with `(<base>+<bonus>)` breakdown.
- `[On Use]` effects: each on its own bold line. If an `[On Use]` effect has sub-bullets (e.g., list of gains), use markdown list below.
- Coin effects: one row per coin. Coin number = sequential position of the coin-effect entry in the wiki text. Multiple effects on the same coin separated by `; `.
- Passive/innate effects (not tagged `[On Use]`): bold line above the coin table (e.g., `**Deal +10% damage** for every...`).

### 5. Defense Skills

```markdown
## Defense Skills
```

Each defense skill:

```markdown
### <Type> [(<State>)]: <Skill Name>

| Offense Level | Base Power | Coin Power |
|---------------|------------|------------|
| <OL> (<Base>+<Bonus>) | <BP> | +<CP> |
```

- Type: Guard, Evade, or Counter.
- State qualifier in parentheses ONLY if identity has multiple states (e.g., `Guard (Iron Maiden)`, `Counter (Flow State)`).
- Include `**Type:** Clashable Guard` / `**Type:** Clashable Counter` line when applicable.
- Include state/assist exclusivity lines (e.g., `**Iron Maiden exclusive Skill**`).
- Include `**Unbreakable Coin**` note when applicable.
- Counter coin effects use the same `| Coin | Effects |` table format as attack skills.

### 6. Combat Passives

```markdown
## Combat Passives

### <Passive Name>

[Ownership requirement line if present, e.g., **(×4 Owned)**]

<Description with bold triggers and markdown lists for sub-effects>

---
```

- Passives without ownership requirements (innate): omit the ownership line.
- Separate passives with `---`.

### 7. Support Passive

```markdown
## Support Passive

### <Passive Name>

**(×<N1> [/ ×<N2>] Owned)**

<Description>

---
```

### 8. Additional Reference (CONDITIONAL)

Include ONLY when skills or passives reference external mechanics not described in the Key Status Effects section or standard game knowledge.

```markdown
## Additional Reference

### <Mechanic Name> (<Context note>)
- <Bullet-point description>
```

Examples: Somatic Frisson-inspiring Melody (buff from passive interaction), Assist Defense.

OMIT this entire section when no external mechanics are referenced.

## Naming Convention (MUST)

Output filename: strip the sinner name and common prefixes, keep the distinguishing identity name.

| Wiki page title | Output filename |
|-----------------|-----------------|
| The House of Spiders: The Ring Apprentice Faust | `Ring_Apprentice_Faust.md` |
| Blade Lineage Salsu Yi Sang | `Blade_Lineage_Salsu_Yi_Sang.md` |
| The Ring Pointillist Student Yi Sang | `Ring_Pointillist_Student_Yi_Sang.md` |

## Data Extraction Notes

- `Base Power` and `Coin Power` on wiki: displayed as `| <BP>+ <CP> |` in a compact table cell. Split into two columns.
- `Atk Weight`: displayed as `Atk Weight ⯀Amt. x<N>` in wiki text. Extract `<N>`.
- `Offense Level`: displayed as `<Total> (<Base>+<Bonus>)` in wiki text. Preserve full format.
- Coin count per skill: count the number of distinct coin-effect paragraphs in the wiki text between one skill's header and the next.
- `[Heads Hit]` effects: treat as coin effects (same as `[On Hit]` but triggered on heads).
- `+N% Damage on Critical Hit`: include as a passive line on the skill (bold, above coin table).
